revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}

Same as {{tlx|Technical}} but for inline usage: indicates that the material immediately preceding this tag may be overly jargonistic, and too technical for the typical readers.  Please improve the text by making it more accessible to more readers (who should not have to be experts already in order to understand our material).

==Usage==

To use the template, enter this after the jargon-laden passage:

<code><nowiki>{{Technical inline|date=</nowiki>{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code>

This template should be used with a date parameter that records when the tag was added in the format "Month YYYY" as displayed above.  If no date is added manually, a [[WP:BOT|bot]] will automatically fill in the gap.

==Parameters==
: {{tlx|Technical inline|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}} 
: {{tlx|Technical inline|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}|reason{{=}}''Your reason here.''}}

==TemplateData==
{{TemplateDataHeader}}
<templatedata>
{
	"params": {
		"date": {
			"label": "Month and year",
			"description": "Provides the month and year of the citation request; e.g., 'January 2013', but not 'jan13'",
			"type": "string",
			"autovalue": "May 2025",
			"suggested": true
		}
	},
	"description": "An inline template indicating that the material immediately preceding it may be overly jargonistic, and too technical for the typical readers.",
	"format": "inline"
}
</templatedata>

== Redirects ==

*{{tlx|technical statement}}
*{{tlx|jargon inline}}
*{{tlx|jargon-inline}}
*{{tlx|jargon-statement}}

